    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1936-11-03T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1936-11-03T00:00:00-05:00" n="561"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d561">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">811.71247H/69½</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Memorandum by the Secretary of State</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">[<placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>,] <date calendar="gregorian" when="1936-11-03">November 3,
                            1936</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>The British Ambassador came in and referred further to our conference of some
                    days ago, in regard to the shipping question in the Australian-New Zealand area
                    which has arisen between certain <pb facs="0796" n="716" xml:id="pg_716"/>
                    American and certain British lines. The Ambassador said that his Government, on
                    his recommendation, was prepared to comply with my suggestion, made in the form
                    of an inquiry during the course of our last conversation, to withdraw the
                    written communication which the British Government as the intermediary of New
                    Zealand had handed to the State Department. This he said, would permit the
                    entire matter to be conducted orally, but naturally in the same manner and, if
                    desired, to the same extent as if it were in writing. I expressed my
                    satisfaction and gratification. The Ambassador said he would call on Mr. Dunn,
                    Chief of the Division of Western European Affairs, and receive from him the
                    instrument of writing and withdraw it.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>C[<hi rend="smallcaps">ordell</hi>] H[<hi rend="smallcaps"
                        >ull</hi>]</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
